---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Paper"
  description="Defense Stacking Against Prompt Injection in LLM Agent Workflows: A Progressive Ablation Study"
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-24 prose">
    <header class="mb-12 not-prose">
      <p class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500 mb-4">
        Technical Paper
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100">
        Defense Stacking Against Prompt Injection in LLM Agent Workflows
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 mt-2">
        A Progressive Ablation Study
      </p>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mt-4 text-sm text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400">
        <span>Misty Step Laboratory</span>
        <span>&middot;</span>
        <span>February 2026</span>
        <span>&middot;</span>
        <span>v1.0</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-4 flex gap-3">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/misty-step/laboratory/blob/master/experiments/prompt-injection-boundary-tags/report/paper.md"
          class="text-sm text-amber-500 hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          View on GitHub &rarr;
        </a>
        <a
          href="/data"
          class="text-sm text-stone-500 hover:text-stone-700 dark:hover:text-stone-300 transition-colors"
        >
          Download data &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <p>
      The full paper is available in our
      <a href="https://github.com/misty-step/laboratory/blob/master/experiments/prompt-injection-boundary-tags/report/paper.md">
        GitHub repository</a>.
      Below is the abstract and key findings. For the interactive version with charts, see the
      <a href="/findings/defense-ablation-synthesis">synthesis findings page</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Abstract</h2>
    <p>
      We present findings from a six-round experimental program measuring prompt-injection defense
      effectiveness in LLM agent workflows. Unlike prior benchmarks that evaluate model vulnerability
      or individual mitigations, we isolate the <strong>marginal contribution of each defense
      layer</strong> through progressive ablation: no defense (raw), boundary tags only, system
      instruction only, instruction + tags, and full stack (instruction + nonce tags + tool-call
      policy filter). Across 3,580 prompt-injection trials spanning 12 models, 12 payload categories,
      and 2 injection channels (direct and retrieval), we find:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>System instructions alone reduce injection success by ~50%.</li>
      <li>Boundary tags alone are unreliable &mdash; they increase injection on some models.</li>
      <li>Instruction + tags achieve ~93% reduction through synergy.</li>
      <li>Full-stack defense reduces injection to &lt;0.2% across all tested conditions.</li>
      <li>Defense ordering transfers across injection channels.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Citation</h2>
    <pre><code>@article{'{'}mistystep2026defense,
  title={'{'}Defense Stacking Against Prompt Injection in LLM Agent Workflows:
         A Progressive Ablation Study{'}'},
  author={'{'}Misty Step Laboratory{'}'},
  year={'{'}2026{'}'},
  month={'{'}February{'}'},
  url={'{'}https://lab.mistystep.com/paper{'}'}
{'}'}</code></pre>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
